{{Quote|Cade. Syn. Deliah. What part of 'safe house' do you not understand?|[[Brogar]]|<ref name="Legacy 2" />}}
'''Brogar's Cantina and Safe House''',<ref name="LECG" /> also known as simply '''Brogar's''', was a combination of a [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] and safe house operated by [[Brogar]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Lok/Legends|Lok]].<ref name="Legacy 2" /> He provided his patrons with security that included bouncers, [[Z65 patrol droid|Z95 patrol guard droids]],<ref name="LECG" /> and at least one [[Unidentified Gotal door attendant|Gotal door attendant]];<ref name="Legacy 2" /> he always had a door attendant monitoring the electronic eye and entry intercom.<ref name="LECG" />

[[File:BrogarsSafeHouseInterior-Legacy2006-2.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Inside view]]
In [[137 ABY]], following the [[Sith–Imperial War]], the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Hosk Trey'lis]] sought sanctuary and transportation there at the same time as [[Naxy Screeger]], who had a [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] placed on him by the [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Rav]]. [[Cade Skywalker]], [[Deliah Blue]], and [[Jariah Syn]] tracked Screeger there to capture him and collect the bounty. In the process, they spotted Trey'lis, who also had a bounty that applied to any Jedi, [[Death/Legends|dead]] or alive.<ref name="Legacy 2" />

{{Loc-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The cantina and safe house appeared in [[Legacy (2006) 2|issue two]] of ''[[Star Wars: Legacy]]''.<ref name="Legacy 2" /> It received an entry in "Chapter XI: The Fringe" of ''[[Legacy Era Campaign Guide]]''.<ref name="LECG" />

